The '''Bounty Hunter Wars''' was a series of inner conflicts between the members of the [[Bounty Hunters' Guild/Legends|Bounty Hunters' Guild]]. It began by [[Prince/Legends|Prince]] [[Xizor/Legends|Xizor]] urging [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] to destroy the guild in order to benefit his struggle for power. After accepting Xizor's idea, Palpatine sent [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] to join the Bounty Hunters' Guild, at the [[Time/Legends|time]] under the leadership of [[Cradossk/Legends|Cradossk]].

After several missions in which Boba Fett prevailed, the members started turning against each other. Soon, the Bounty Hunters' Guild was split into the [[True Guild]] and the [[Guild Reform Committee]]. Not satisfied with the results, Xizor, once again, persuaded Palpatine to follow his plan. This time, Xizor had Palpatine place a huge [[Bounty/Legends|bounty]] on [[Trhin Voss'on't]]'s head. Supposedly, Trhin had killed everyone aboard his [[Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]], evacuated himself with a huge sum of money, and gone into hiding. All of the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] took up the job, and greed killed most of them off; or, at least, destroyed the remaining factions of the Bounty Hunters' Guild.

